I86Ex. Ord. No. T112675K. Establishing the National Space Council

I21Ex. Ord. No. 12675, Apr. 20, 1989, 54 F.R. 17691, as amended by Ex. Ord. No. 12712, Apr. 26, 1990, 55 F.R. 18095; Ex. Ord. No. 12869, ÿ1A4(f), Sept. 30, 1993, 58 F.R. 51752, provided:

I21By the authority vested in me as President by the Constitution and laws of the United States of America, and in order to provide a coordinated process for developing a national space policy and strategy and for monitoring its implementation, it is hereby ordered as follows:

I21T4SectionK 1. T3Establishment and Composition of the National Space Council.

I21(a) There is established the National Space Council (``the Council'').

I21(b) The Council shall be composed of the following members:

I21(1) The Vice President, who shall be Chairman of the Council;

I21(2) The Secretary of State;

I21(3) The Secretary of the Treasury;

I21(4) The Secretary of Defense;

I21(5) The Secretary of Commerce;

I21(6) The Secretary of Transportation;

I21(7) The Secretary of Energy;

I21(8) The Director of the Office of Management and Budget;

I21(9) The Chief of Staff to the President;

I21(10) The Assistant to the President for National Security Affairs;

I21(11) The Assistant to the President for Science and Technology;

I21(12) The Director of Central Intelligence; and

I21(13) The Administrator of the National Aeronautics and Space Administration.

I21(c) The Chairman shall, from time to time, invite the following to participate in meetings of the Council:

I21(1) The Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff; and

I21(2) The heads of other executive departments and agencies and other senior officials in the Executive Office of the President.

I21T4SecK. 2. T3Functions of the CouncilK. (a) The Council shall advise and assist the President on national space policy and strategy, and perform such other duties as the President may from time to time prescribe.

I21(b) In addition, the Council is directed to:

I21(1) review United States Government space policy, including long-range goals, and develop a strategy for national space activities;

I21(2) develop recommendations for the President on space policy and space-related issues;

I21(3) monitor and coordinate implementation of the objectives of the President's national space policy by executive departments and agencies; and

I21(4) foster close coordination, cooperation, and technology and information exchange among the civil, national security, and commercial space sectors, and facilitate resolution of differences concerning major space and space-related policy issues.

I21(c) The creation and operation of the Council shall not interfere with existing lines of authority and responsibilities in the departments and agencies.

I21T4SecK. 3. T3Responsibilities of the ChairmanK. (a) The Chairman shall serve as the President's principal advisor on national space policy and strategy.

I21(b) The Chairman shall, in consultation with the members of the Council, establish procedures for the Council and establish the agenda for Council activities.

I21(c) The Chairman shall report to the President on the activities and recommendations of the Council. The Chairman shall advise the Council as appropriate regarding the President's directions with respect to the Council's activities and national space policy generally.

I21(d) The Chairman shall authorize the establishment of such committees of the Council, including an executive committee, and of such working groups, composed of senior designees of the Council members and of other officials invited to participate in Council meetings, as he deems necessary or appropriate for the efficient conduct of Council functions.

I21T4SecK. 4. T3National Space Policy Planning ProcessK. (a) The Council will establish a process for developing and monitoring the implementation of national space policy and strategy.

I21(b) To implement this process, each agency represented on the Council shall provide such information regarding its current and planned space activities as the Chairman shall request.

I21(c) The head of each executive department and agency shall ensure that its space-related activities conform to national space policy and strategy.

I21T4SecK. 5. [Revoked by Ex. Ord. No. 12869, ÿ1A4(f), Sept. 30, 1993, 58 F.R. 51752.]

I21T4SecK. 6. T3Microgravity Research BoardK. Section 1(c) of Executive Order No. 12660 is amended by deleting ``Economic Policy Council'' and inserting in lieu thereof ``National Space Council.''

I21T4SecK. 7. T3Administrative ProvisionsK. (a) The Office of Administration in the Executive Office of the President shall provide the Council with such administrative support on a reimbursable basis as may be necessary for the performance of the functions of the Council.

I21(b) The President shall appoint an Executive Secretary who shall appoint such staff as may be necessary to assist in the performance of the Council's functions.

I21(c) All Federal departments, agencies, and interagency councils and committees having an impact on space policy shall extend, as appropriate, such cooperation and assistance to the Council as is necessary to carry out its responsibilities under this order.

I21(d) The head of each agency serving on the Council or represented on any working group or committee of the Council shall provide such administrative support as may be necessary, in accordance with law and subject to the availability of appropriations, to enable the agency head or its representative to carry out his responsibilities.

I21T4SecK. 8. T3ReportK. The Council shall submit an annual report setting forth its assessment of and recommendations for the space policy and strategy of the United States Government.

