I89. Vision for space exploration

I11(a) T4In GeneralK._The Administrator shall establish a program to develop a sustained human presence on the Moon, including a robust precursor program, to promote exploration, science, commerce, and United States preeminence in space, and as a stepping-stone to future exploration of Mars and other destinations. The Administrator is further authorized to develop and conduct appropriate international collaborations in pursuit of these goals.

I11(b) T4MilestonesK._The Administrator shall manage human space flight programs to strive to achieve the following milestones (in conformity with section 70502 of this title):

I12(1) Returning Americans to the Moon no later than 2020.

I12(2) Launching the Crew Exploration Vehicle as close to 2010 as possible.

I12(3) Increasing knowledge of the impacts of long duration stays in space on the human body using the most appropriate facilities available, including the International Space Station.

I12(4) Enabling humans to land on and return from Mars and other destinations on a timetable that is technically and fiscally possible.

