I80ÿ1A50101

I89. Definitions

I11In this chapter:

I12(1) T4Commercial providerK._The term ``commercial provider'' means any person providing space transportation services or other space-related activities, primary control of which is held by persons other than Federal, State, local, and foreign governments.

I12(2) T4PayloadK._The term ``payload'' means anything that a person undertakes to transport to, from, or within outer space, or in suborbital trajectory, by means of a space transportation vehicle, but does not include the space transportation vehicle itself except for its components which are specifically designed or adapted for that payload.

I12(3) T4Space-related activitiesK._The term ``space-related activities'' includes research and development, manufacturing, processing, service, and other associated and support activities.

I12(4) T4Space transportation servicesK._The term ``space transportation services'' means the preparation of a space transportation vehicle and its payloads for transportation to, from, or within outer space, or in suborbital trajectory, and the conduct of transporting a payload to, from, or within outer space, or in suborbital trajectory.

I12(5) T4Space transportation vehicleK._The term ``space transportation vehicle'' means any vehicle constructed for the purpose of operating in, or transporting a payload to, from, or within, outer space, or in suborbital trajectory, and includes any component of such vehicle not specifically designed or adapted for a payload.

I12(6) T4StateK._The term ``State'' means each of the several States of the Union, the District of Columbia, the Commonwealth of Puerto Rico, the Virgin Islands, Guam, American Samoa, the Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands, and any other commonwealth, territory, or possession of the United States.

I12(7) T4United states commercial providerK._The term ``United States commercial provider'' means a commercial provider, organized under the laws of the United States or of a State, that is_

I13(A) more than 50 percent owned by United States nationals; or

I13(B) a subsidiary of a foreign company and the Secretary of Transportation finds that_

I14(i) such subsidiary has in the past evidenced a substantial commitment to the United States market through_

I16(I) investments in the United States in long-term research, development, and manufacturing (including the manufacture of major components and subassemblies); and

I16(II) significant contributions to employment in the United States; and

Q04

I14(ii) the country or countries in which such foreign company is incorporated or organized, and, if appropriate, in which it principally conducts its business, affords reciprocal treatment to companies described in subparagraph (A) comparable to that afforded to such foreign company's subsidiary in the United States, as evidenced by_

I16(I) providing comparable opportunities for companies described in subparagraph (A) to participate in Government-sponsored research and development similar to that authorized under this chapter;

I16(II) providing no barriers, to companies described in subparagraph (A) with respect to local investment opportunities, that are not provided to foreign companies in the United States; and

I16(III) providing adequate and effective protection for the intellectual property rights of companies described in subparagraph (A).

