I11(c) T4Civil PenaltyK._(1) After notice and an opportunity for a hearing on the record, a person the Secretary finds to have violated subsection (a) of this section is liable to the United States Government for a civil penalty of not more than $100,000. A separate violation occurs for each day the violation continues.

I11(2) In conducting a hearing under paragraph (1) of this subsection, the Secretary may_

I12(A) subpena witnesses and records; and

I12(B) enforce a subpena in an appropriate district court of the United States.

Q04

I11(3) The Secretary shall impose the civil penalty by written notice. The Secretary may compromise or remit a penalty imposed, or that may be imposed, under this section.

I11(4) The Secretary shall recover a civil penalty not paid after the penalty is final or after a court enters a final judgment for the Secretary.

